Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as hypergraphs are a topic in discrete mathematics and this paper provides an introduction and review of the topic. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as hypergraphs are used to model complex networks in various fields including social and information networks. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possible category as hypergraphs have applications in computational geometry, such as in hypergraph partitioning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as hypergraphs can be used to represent data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions some unpublished work on the visualization of large hypergraphs.
